{
  "_comment": "Resource-node group + variant catalog (the *where*). Server loads this at boot; cache-builder projects the client subset into pokemon_data.bin. Two group shapes: DEF-BACKED skill groups whose variants carry `ref` (a resource_defs.json def name) + `id` + `sprite` + `weight` — their economy (tool/hp_max/respawn_ms/loot/xp/level) lives on the def — and INLINE OBSTACLE groups (HM gates, Strength) whose variants carry only `id` + `sprite` and whose single-swing economy stays on the group (group-level respawn_ms). area_pool groups bind into Resource_Areas polygons whose MAX_ACTIVE caps how many of the pool's nodes are live at once; which ones are live is mining-driven (depleting an active node promotes a dormant sibling). Depletion is always per-player; the PerPlayerRespawn ticker refreshes a depleted node in-session for that one player. Collision is always the single anchor tile; the sprite renders bottom-flush. Artists ship sprites at final on-screen size. Action / depleted strips are 4-frame horizontal sheets (ACTION_FRAMES = 4). See docs/game-server/RESOURCE_NODES.md §4.2 / §4.3.",
